<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98051683215940></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98051683215940><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=7&mid=98051683215940>RE: help with starting a cleric</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=607><span id=Sage>Gedran</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>97 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jan 26th 1:50 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The races that are considered by most to be the two best for being a cleric are Dwarves and High Elves.  Pretty much, if your playing a good race cleric, your already a holy, spell casting, noble, and non evil (the intelligent part is up to you).  Spells can all be found at, WWW.everlore.com, They pretty much have a complete description of each one.<br><br>Gedran<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
