	   <tr><td colspan=2>I personally like tailoring and I am a high elf cleric as well. Granted, I've been told by my "elders" that generally people pick up a trade at higher levels due to boredom and because most are quite expensive, like smithing. Not that I necessarilly agree at all, but I can see their point. Thus, why I chose tailoring. It's easy, it's cheap, and most of the resources can be found whilst hunting. There are some great sites that support tailoring as well, most of which you can even find linked off of this site. Above all however, research the trades. Especially if you are an avid rp'er...find what fits your character's persona and what you think sounds fun, because you'll be spending A LOT of time building that skill.<br>Take care, and best of luck to you in whatever path you so may choose.<br><br>~Alyra<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
