	   <tr><td colspan=2>I think the best choice for playing a character is the dwarf. These are the rankings in which i think makes a great cleric.<br>1. DWARF - Dwarves have the highest strength and stanima whch means better fighting and you can use heavier armor. They also have good wisdom which means more spells. <br>2. HIGH ELF - The best wisdom out of any of these classes. Wisdom means more mana and clerics need mana more than any other race. I also think that Greater Faydark is one of the best places for anyone to start from.<br>3. DARK ELF - Dark elves have one of my favorite attributes. UTLRAVISION!! You need to see to play and dark elves can see well even in the darkest dungeons. They are also a good mix of wisdom and dexterity. The one thing that confuses me is that why is a pure evil race able to have god-loving clerics. <br>4. HALFLING - The one thing that halflings have more than anyone is dexterity. This means less spell interrupts from opposing forces. That is about all alflings have going for them except of course Misty Thicket.<br>5. ERUDITE - Good wisdom, great intellegence, horrible strength, worse vision and an even worse starting zone. Tox Forest is dark and Erudites can't see. NOT A GOOD MIX!<br>6. HUMAN - A well rounded out class. I just don't like them because they can't see. Getting "halo of light" will solve that problem, BUT YOU HAVE TO WAIT 14 LVLS.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
