	   <tr><td colspan=2>At level 20, sure pull out that mace when u have a chance.  Just be sure your charged up and ready to go.  I still, at times, take aim with my morning star. Although, its just for a laugh and a change from the usual .. bigger laugh if I can actually get the killing blow.  <br>But the simple fact of the matter is a lv 20 warrior can out melee a lv 50 cleric. We are given no dammage bonuses or extra atacks, and our melee skill caps out way under a tanks. <br>Now, if I take out my mace as soon as a mob turns to run I may get lucky and do 40 whole points of dammage to its 400 or so HP's still left ~ so yes, if you meleeing at higher levels and OOM or LOM a good group would smile and say sorry, we have another cleric comming now. <br>Wait till a Mob is double atacking for 100+/- each round and do a little math you fill find casting a Stun or DD will surely aid you better than that old dusty mace.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
