	   <tr><td colspan=2>Aye... You'll be wasting mana if you're at 100% and no one is harmed yet.. Depending on the circumstance I'll Wrath if at 100%, melee early on if warrented or if its blue, take some hits for the tanks or if a mob gets onto a caster. Yes we heal but if your group makes you only heal, then they have no idea WHAT a cleric can do.<br><br>We can stun opposing mobs (especially spell casters), heal, buff, etc. it ALSO depends on the race of the cleric. Erudites and HE are more support casters... We Dwarves favour a more "in it's face" clerical casting and combat (justly known as Brells' Battle Clerics). It's all situational, and nobody but you knows how to play your cleric. Our job is to make sure nobody dies (or the fewest). How we get that job done is our business. It can involve DD spells, stuns, heals, melee, and buffs (3 types) or a combination of all 5.<br><br>Durus Stoneguard<br>Initiate of the 32nd Mystery of Brell Serilis<br>Povar<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
